using UnityEngine;

public class ShaderError : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Applying a shader to a sprite without proper setup
        GetComponent<SpriteRenderer>().material.shader = Shader.Find("Unlit/Color");
        // May not work if shader isn't imported
    }
}

phase2.explanation:
Shader.Find might return null if the shader name is wrong.

**The fix:**
```csharp
Shader shader = Shader.Find("Unlit/Color");
if (shader != null)
{
    GetComponent<SpriteRenderer>().material.shader = shader;
}
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"Always check if Shader.Find returns a valid shader."
